OL,6,FToday, Lee's mother said greater
OL,7,Fawareness and education about the harm
OL,8,Fcarrying a knife can cause is needed.
OL,10,F"Lee was larger than life. A gentle
OL,11,Fgiant with a heart of gold. He would
OL,12,Fdo anything for anybody," Joanne said.
OL,13,F"He was loved by everybody. He was
OL,14,Fjust that type of person.
OL,16,F"Our lives are in tatters to be
OL,17,Fhonest. I don't think it'll be the
OL,18,Fsame ever again. I don't think any
OL,19,Fmother gets over the loss of her only
OL,20,Fchild."
